Which command is used to display the last 10 lines of a text file in Linux?
a) head
b) more
c) tail
d) less

c) tail

In Linux, what command is used to change the password for a user?
a) passwd
b) passchange
c) userpasswd
d) chpasswd

a) passwd

Which of the following commands would you use to display the current working directory in Linux?
a) pwd
b) dir
c) ls
d) cd

a)pwd

What command would you use to make a copy of a file named "file1.txt" into a new file named "file2.txt"?
a) cp file1.txt file2.txt
b) mv file1.txt file2.txt
c) copy file1.txt file2.txt
d) duplicate file1.txt file2.txt

a) cp file1.txt file2.txt

Which of the following commands would you use to list all users currently logged into the system?
a) list
b) who
c) users
d) logged

b) who

In Linux, what is the purpose of the "chmod" command?
a) Change file ownership
b) Change file permissions
c) Change file location
d) Change file type

b) Change file permissions

What command would you use to search for a specific string within a file?
a) find
b) grep
c) search
d) locate

b) grep

Which of the following commands would you use to create a symbolic link named "link" pointing to a file named "target"?
a) ln -s target link
b) sym link target
c) ln -t target link
d) link -s target

c) ln -t target link

In Linux, what does the command "echo $PATH" display?
a) The current date and time
b) The contents of the PATH environment variable
c) The system's IP address
d) The current user's home directory

b) The contents of the PATH environment variable


What command would you use to shut down a Linux system immediately?
a) shutdown -h now
b) poweroff
c) halt
d) shutdown -r now

b) poweroff
